name: integer_u16_signed_maximum
description: |
  This is 32767, the greatest u16 value that is also representable as i16.
  Adding 1 sets the high bit and reaches 32768, the first u16 value outside the
  i16 positive range. The adjacent pair targets off-by-one range checks,
  narrowing conversions, and code that mistakes the high bit for a sign bit.
format: hex
decode-as: u16
pair:
  - with: high-bit.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u16"
  - "signed-maximum"
  - "boundary"
  - "conversion"
  - "sign-bit"
  - "off-by-one"
---
ff 7f   # 32767
